-- U.K. Says Coupon Payments on Tier 2 Capital Are Tax-Deductible
-- B y   G o n z a l o   V i n a
-- 2012-10-26T12:17:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-26/u-k-says-coupon-payments-on-tier-2-capital-are-tax-deductible.html
The U.K. Treasury said coupon
payments on Tier 2 capital that banks are required to hold can
be offset against corporation tax.  Treasury Minister Greg Clark said the treatment of the
coupon clarified uncertainty created by the Capital Requirements
Directive IV. He made the comments in a  written statement to
Parliament  in  London  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gonzalo Vina in London at 
 gvina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net  